name: Hilton Garden Inn Bali Ngurah Rai Airport
detail: We chose to stay here for one night before leaving on a flight the next day, and we are so glad that we did! Room was perfect and the breakfast was great (excellent coffee- something that I didn’t realize would be difficult to come by at hotels in Bali. The pool is stunning and huge. I ordered an amazing cocktail to the pool - a raspberry Tom Collins. Great business centre to print boarding passes. A+!

name: W Bali - Seminyak
detail: There are a lot of really nice things about the W but there are some downsides too. The good: The interior design is very well considered and we appreciated the details. Rooms were excellent, the communal areas were breathtaking and very ... 'cool' (horrifically general word but I think this is what they're intending it to be). The pools were nice and the restaurants were pretty well designed also. The best thing was the sunset - breathtakingly beautiful! Room service was reasonably good also, once or twice they forgot something but on the whole it was above par. The bad: The concierge Whatever whenever never worked - it became a joke that whatever whenever meant that they'd do whatever they felt like whenever they could be bothered. I think this was mostly because they were so understaffed that random staff trying to help jumped in and confused everything. Next, the outdoor areas are badly designed and tiny, for a hotel this size it needs at least 2x the outdoor space to function at a 5 star level. We found ourselves always messing around trying to find available poolside space as if it were a nasty 3 star all inclusive resort. There were no private places however I think if you take a villa you get some garden area but no beachside. The cocktails are totally watered down overpriced for bali. I know that this is an international grade hotel however the drinks to standard as you'd expect globally but were priced about the similarly Lastly: there wasnt really anything balinese, which was a huge shame. Bali is such a beautiful place-attitude, culture, art & craft, it would have been nice if some aspect of this was incorporated -this hotel could have been anywhere in the world as nothing of Bali really came through. Don't be put off, if you're looking for a place which is beautifully designed, beside a beach (where you cant swim) and amongst other premium grade hipster wannabes then this is really your home.

name: Sunday Hotel Arshika Sunset Road
detail: Location, staff and the room was excellent as I expected.

name: Holiday Inn Express Baruna Bali By IHG
detail: This is my 2nd time I visit this hotel. I love this hotel because it has comfy bed and Coin laundry :-) do not have to worry run out of clothes after many activities in Bali.

name: Jimbaran Bay Beach Resort & Spa by Prabhu
detail: Like most of the hotels in Bali, its always great value for the money, that is, if you come from abroad. The location is a mixed blessing, while its right across from the beach, there is basically nothing to speak of in the vicinity, other than a few seafood places with mediocre service and inflated prices. Staff are great, again, Balinese hospitality!!

name: Le Méridien Bali Jimbaran
detail: The room was big and nicely designed. The kids love the pool!! The pool is actually one of the best one we have seen in Bali even compared to the pool at Conrad Bali, Grand Hyatt Nusa Dua, Intercon, Nikko, etc etc. Sure, the pools in the other hotels are bigger but this one has a very nice feel to it and it is a salt water lagoon pool so you dont have that strong chlorine taste. The hotel has a nice feel to it. Its not huge but its just the right size. The staff is attentive and very friendly. One day the housekeeping forgot to clean up our room and i made a complain about it and the next day the hotel put a pair of stuffed animal for our kids with a handwritten note from the General Manager. Now thats what i call service! Overall, we love the hotel and will definitely come back again there and will recommend this hotel to travelers with small kids.

name: Holiday Inn Bali Sanur By IHG
detail: This hotel makes my bali experience a thousand times better

name: Hotel Indigo Bali Seminyak Beach By IHG
detail: Extremely friendly and accommodating staffs, tasty food, very good drinks. We really loved and enjoyed their breakfast buffet so much. We've been traveling around the world a lot and we have stayed in a few hotels in Bali and all we can say is Hotel Indigo has the best breakfast buffet with top notch customer service. During breakfast you can request your own fresh juice like you can choose whatever fruits you want and as many fruits as you want and they will freshly make juice for you. Their coffee and tea selections during breakfast was also very nice. You can choose whatever type of coffee you want be it mocha, latte, cappuccino, americano, expresso etc. The waiters/waitresses will come check on you once in awhile to offer more coffee/tea. The afternoon tea set at the Pottery Cafe is also very nice. It includes unlimited coffee and tea and you can change your drink around if you want to try different drinks and it's for free (coffee and tea only)

name: InterContinental Bali Resort By IHG
detail: Has everything you would want. Larger rooms than other hotels in Bali costing much more. Best deal in Bali for the money. Not far from Kuta or the airport too. You can even see the planes land from the beach but can't hear them. Many places to eat and drink cheaper just to the left of the beach. Walking about 2km to the right will bring you to several Jimbaran Beach seafood restaurants right on the beach. Metered taxis are readily available on call from the transport desk if you can't do the walking. ATMs, restaurants, small shops and mini marts are also just across the street.

name: Grand Barong Resort Bali Managed by Soscomma
detail: location is great. Not to far from the nightlife and beach. I liked the idea of the 2 pools. A quiet one where I can relax. The other was more of a party area which suited my younger friends. Staff are helpful and friendly. Room was comfortable. The only fault I could pick with this hotel was that the Internet in the room was not good. I need to work online now and again which I could not do in the comfort of my room. I had to sit in the restaurant for a good signal when I needed to do work. I found this problem in most of the 4 star hotels in Bali. Apart from that I enjoyed my stay
